com.nevermindsoftware.urlparser

Class Url

  • com.nevermindsoftware.urlparser.Url

  • public class Url

    Data class containing a parsed url. The queryParams property is lazily evaluated from the queryStr

    • Constructor Detail

      • Url

        public Url(@Nullable
           java.lang.String raw,
           @Nullable
           java.lang.String scheme,
           @Nullable
           java.lang.String host,
           @Nullable
           java.lang.String tld,
           @Nullable
           java.lang.String path,
           @Nullable
           java.lang.String queryStr,
           @NotNull
           java.util.List<java.lang.String> subDomains)

        Data class containing a parsed url. The queryParams property is lazily evaluated from the queryStr

        Parameters:
        raw - The raw string used to parse this Url
        scheme - The url scheme (e.g. http, https, ftp)
        host - The url host, ie the last group before the TLD
        tld - The TLD for this Url, as specified by the Suffix List
        path - The path following the TLD. Prefixed with "/"
        queryStr - The raw query string. Prefixed with "?"
        subDomains - A list of sub domain groups, not including the host (e.g. a.b.c.example.com = a,b,c)
